    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Nonchalance Is Back</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Bill Cunningham</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cunningham, Bill</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Photos of evening wear outfits seen in New York City (On the Street column) (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The daytime blouse worn without a jacket was part of the sportswear revolution of the late 1930's. The evening shirt was popularized by the Gibson girl circa 1900, when the man's shirt, recut, became an alluring style. This fall, the silk blouse, top row, is being embraced as a daytime look, and taffeta shirts, bottom row, are being worn for evening with long skirts or trousers, or sometimes as a jacket over a dress.</p>
      </block>
